== Art life == Ali Erturk is also known for his landscape and cityscapes photographs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.biochem.mpg.de/5100363/ali_ertuerk|title=Ali Ertürk|website=www.biochem.mpg.de|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://500px.com/alierturk|title=Ali Erturk|website=500px.com|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/alierturkphotography/|title=Ali Erturk Photography|website=www.facebook.com|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref> As of 2018, he had 3 exhibitions (2008 Munich, 2012 San Francisco, 2015 Munich).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/muenchen/martinsried-mit-eigenen-augen-1.2723896|title=Mit eigenen Augen|last=Martinsried|first=Annette Jäger|date=2015-11-05|newspaper=[[Süddeutsche Zeitung]]|trans-title=With your own eyes|language=German|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180327210617/http://www.sueddeutsche.de/muenchen/martinsried-mit-eigenen-augen-1.2723896|archive-date=2018-03-27|access-date=2018-03-27}}</ref>
