'''Goldstone Catena''' ('''Goldstone Vallis''' until March 2013) is a catena on [[Mercury (planet)|Mercury]] located at 15.8 S, 31.7 W. It is named after [[Goldstone Observatory]]. While it superficially resembles a [[graben]], it is a chain of overlapping secondary craters.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://astrogeology.usgs.gov/Projects/PlanetaryMapping/DIGGEOL/mercury/h6/h6.pdf| title=Geologic Map of the Kuiper (H-6) Quadrangle of Mercury| first=R.A.| last= De Hon| author2= D.H. Scott |author3=J.R. Underwood, Jr.| date=1981| format=PDF}}</ref>

