{{infobox person/Wikidata | fetchwikidata=ALL}}

'''Harri Lorenzi''' (born 1949) is a [[Brazil]]ian [[agronomy|agronomic]] [[engineering|engineer]], author on trees of the [[Atlantic Mata]] and a collaborating [[agronomist]] of the [[garden]] of [[Fazenda Cresciumal]], Ruy De Souza Queiroz.  Between his workmanships, he published four books in the end of the 1990s, they are:  ''Brazilian palms'', ''Brazilian Trees'' (1 and 2, also in English),<ref>{{cite web|last=Cannon II|first=Bob G.|title=Book Review: Brazilian Trees|url=http://www.quisqualis.com/BrazilainTreesReview.html|work=quisqualis.com|accessdate=11 December 2010}}</ref> ''Tropical Plants of Burle Marx'' and ''Brazilian Ornamental Plants''.

